  "text": "## gRPC Error Status Propagation Patterns Across Three Go Services\n\n### Kubernetes (K8s) Approach\n\nKubernetes uses a **HTTP-to-gRPC translation pattern** in the streaming error handler. The key file is `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go` which implements `WriteError()` function (lines 33-51). This function:\n\n1. **Extracts gRPC status**: Uses `grpcstatus.FromError(err)` to extract the gRPC status from an error\n2. **Maps to HTTP**: Switches on `s.Code()` to map gRPC codes to HTTP status codes:\n   - `codes.NotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound` (404)\n   - `codes.ResourceExhausted` → `http.StatusTooManyRequests` (429) with Retry-After header\n   - Default → `http.StatusInternalServerError` (500)\n3. **Writes response**: Calls `w.WriteHeader(status)` and `w.Write()` to send the HTTP response\n\nGRPC errors are created directly in service implementations. For example, in `test/e2e/storage/drivers/csi-test/mock/service/node.go` (lines 220-221):\n- `status.Error(codes.Internal, msg)` creates errors for internal failures\n- `status.Error(codes.NotFound, msg)` for missing resources\n\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/cri-api/pkg/errors/errors.go` file provides the `IsNotFound()` helper (lines 44-54) to check if an error has `codes.NotFound` status, showing the checking pattern.\n\nRate limiting errors are created using predefined constants in `pkg/kubelet/apis/grpc/ratelimit.go` (line 31): `ErrorLimitExceeded = status.Error(codes.ResourceExhausted, \"rejected by rate limit\")`\n\n### Grafana Approach\n\nGrafana uses a **layered error translation pattern** with multiple conversion points:\n\n1. **Unified Resource Error Handling** (`pkg/storage/unified/resource/errors.go`):\n   - `AsErrorResult()` (lines 122-165) converts various error types to `resourcepb.ErrorResult`\n   - Handles both Kubernetes API errors and gRPC status errors\n   - For gRPC errors (line 156-159): Extracts status with `grpcstatus.FromError()` and uses `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode()` to convert codes to HTTP status\n   - Returns `resourcepb.ErrorResult` with HTTP status code (32-bit integer)\n\n2. **Direct gRPC Error Creation** (`pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go`):\n   - Creates gRPC errors directly throughout the authentication interceptor\n   - `status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"token required\")` (line 71)\n   - `status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)` (line 118, 123)\n   - `status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, ...)` for various auth failures (lines 66, 79, 104, 114, 144, 149, 153)\n\n3. **Downstream Error Translation** (`pkg/tsdb/influxdb/fsql/fsql.go`, lines 58-72):\n   - Extracts gRPC status from downstream service errors: `status.FromError(err)`\n   - Switches on error code to map to backend response status:\n     - `codes.InvalidArgument` → `backend.StatusBadRequest`\n     - `codes.PermissionDenied` → `backend.StatusForbidden`\n     - `codes.NotFound` → `backend.StatusNotFound`\n     - `codes.Unavailable` → `http.StatusServiceUnavailable`\n     - `codes.Unauthenticated` → `backend.StatusUnauthorized`\n\n4. **Resource Authorization Errors** (`pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go`, lines 596-598, 1022-1024):\n   - Creates `status.Error(codes.NotFound, \"unsupported resource\")` for missing resources\n\n### etcd Approach\n\netcd uses a **centralized error mapping pattern** with pre-defined gRPC errors and a conversion function:\n\n1. **Pre-defined gRPC Errors** (`api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`, lines 23-98):\n   - Defines all gRPC errors as constants with specific status codes:\n   - `ErrGRPCEmptyKey = status.Error(codes.InvalidArgument, ...)`  (line 24)\n   - `ErrGRPCLeaseNotFound = status.Error(codes.NotFound, ...)`  (line 36)\n   - `ErrGRPCMemberNotFound = status.Error(codes.NotFound, ...)`  (line 46)\n   - `ErrGRPCRequestTooManyRequests = status.Error(codes.ResourceExhausted, ...)`  (line 57)\n   - `ErrGRPCPermissionDenied = status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)`  (line 69)\n   - Uses `status.Error()` to create errors with appropriate code and message\n\n2. **Error String Mapping** (`api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`, lines 100-165):\n   - Maps error description strings back to gRPC error objects for round-trip conversion\n   - Enables reconstructing the same gRPC error from its string representation\n\n3. **Server-side Error Translation** (`server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go`, lines 35-108):\n   - `toGRPCErrorMap` (lines 35-96) maps internal server errors to gRPC errors:\n     - `membership.ErrIDNotFound` → `rpctypes.ErrGRPCMemberNotFound`\n     - `mvcc.ErrCompacted` → `rpctypes.ErrGRPCCompacted`\n     - `errors.ErrNoLeader` → `rpctypes.ErrGRPCNoLeader`\n   - `togRPCError()` function (lines 98-108) performs the actual translation:\n     - Allows context cancellation/deadline errors to pass through\n     - Uses the map to convert, or defaults to `status.Error(codes.Unknown, ...)`\n\n4. **RPC Handler Integration** (`server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/auth.go`, `key.go`, `member.go`, `lease.go`, `maintenance.go`):\n   - All RPC handlers call `togRPCError()` when returning errors\n   - Example from auth.go (line 37-38): `if err != nil { return nil, togRPCError(err) }`\n   - Example from member.go (line 104-106): `if err != nil { return nil, togRPCError(err) }`\n\n5. **HTTP Bridge** (`server/etcdserver/api/etcdhttp/peer.go`, lines 152-159):\n   - Translates gRPC errors to HTTP responses for HTTP endpoints\n   - Maps specific error types to HTTP status codes:\n     - `membership.ErrIDNotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`\n     - `membership.ErrMemberNotLearner` → `http.StatusPreconditionFailed`\n\n### Key Differences\n\n**Kubernetes**: Uses inline error creation at service boundaries and translation at the streaming handler layer.\n\n**Grafana**: Uses both direct gRPC error creation in interceptors and unified conversion functions for downstream error translation.\n\n**etcd**: Uses a centralized, declarative approach with pre-defined error constants and a single conversion function (`togRPCError`) that all RPC handlers invoke consistently.\n\nThe etcd approach is the most maintainable because it centralizes error definitions and conversions, while Kubernetes and Grafana distribute error creation throughout their codebases and translate at multiple points (interceptors, handlers, and gateway layers)."
