) that all RPC handlers invoke consistently.\n\nThe etcd approach is the most maintainable because it centralizes error definitions and conversions, while Kubernetes and Grafana distribute error creation throughout their codebases and translate at multiple points (interceptors, handlers, and gateway layers)."
